  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dda \u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dae\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dda \u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The country's economy collapsed due to the fault of three governments",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member of Parliament Acharya Nalaka Godaheva said that the country's economy did not collapse during the reign of Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa, and that all the three governments that came to power after the war should be held responsible for it.",
        "During 2009-2015, the country's debt increased from 2200 billion rupees to 7400 billion rupees, the MP said, adding that it was the Rajapaksa government that started taking short-term commercial loans at high interest rates.",
        "Mr. Godaheva mentioned that the government of Mr. Mahinda Rajapaksa continued to take loans and implemented development projects that did not generate income and that there was a lot of waste and corruption behind the infrastructure development.",
        "He said that the Maithripala Sirisena and Ranil Wickremesinghe governments that came to power and the previous government committed more waste and corruption than the previous government, and during that time the debt increased from 7400 billion rupees to 13,000 billion rupees.",
        "The MP said that the group that worked hard to bring Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to power had prepared an economic management plan, but after he came to power, the people who prepared the plan were forgotten and the economy was handed over to the same people who had managed the country's economy before 2015, so the desired goals were not achieved."
      ],
